        assert.ok(Math.abs(result.im) < 1e-10, 'Imaginary part should be approximately 0');

        done();
    });

})
```

The key change is replacing the strict equality check for the imaginary part with a tolerance-based check using `Math.abs(result.im) < 1e-10`. This accounts for tiny floating-point precision errors that can occur in mathematical computations while still verifying that the imaginary part is effectively zero.

